records.addlTxt:
Defendant Amanda L Doucette in court with attorney Kelsey Loshaw.  Kevin Michael Osborne appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count 1 of the amended information.  Court finds defendant guilty.  The Defendant was sentenced to the following:

Count #1:

WITHHELD SENTENCE:

TERM OF PROBATION:  2 YEARS; (credit 0 days);

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  
*AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
*Absolute Sobriety;  Random U.A.'s ; 
*No Use or Possession of alcohol, controlled substances or drug paraphernalia.
*No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
*Any valid prescription drugs must be taken only in the manner in which they are prescribed.
*Inform Agent of all prescriptions
*Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
*Maintain full time employment and/or combination of schooling 
*No contact with:  co-defendant - with the exception to facilitate any issue regarding the child in common and must be approved by agent; 
*Defendant may have contact with the victim Keith D. with continued approval of the victim and the agent. 
*DNA sample to be provided if not yet previously done.
*Obtain GED/HSED. 
*No association with known drug users or dealers and no contact at any place where illegal drugs are purchased, used, stored, packages or distributed. 
RESTITUTION:  $100.00 (to Keith D. to be paid as a condition of probation - restitution to be paid before costs or fines);

COURT COSTS:  $278.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation);

DNA SURCHARGE:  $250.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation);

CONDITION TIME: 30 Days, STAYED; to be used at agent's discretion.  Agent to determine with or without non working hours.  

Felony warnings, voting rights and firearms warnings given.

Expunction is conditionally granted upon verification of completion of sentence, payment of all costs/fees and no new law violations.
